FBIS4-11906 "drnes064_k_94003" FBIS-NES-94-064 Daily Report 3 Apr 1994 IRAQ Gunmen Kill AFP Correspondent, Bodyguard in Ambush Gunmen Kill AFP Correspondent, Bodyguard in Ambush NC0304195794 Paris AFP in English 1936 GMT 3 Apr 94 NC0304195794 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Nicosia, April 3 (AFP) -- Gunmen shot dead an AFP correspondent and her bodyguard in an ambush near al-Sulaymaniyah in Iraqi Kurdistan on Sunday [3 April], UN aid workers said. Lissy Schmidt, a 35-year-old German, was travelling by car with her Iraqi Kurdish bodyguard when they were attacked east of the city, Steven Allen of UNICEF in the northern Iraqi town of Irbil told AFP by telephone. The ambush occurred at 1:00 p.m. (0900 GMT). Schmidt was the only foreign journalist permanently based in Iraqi Kurdistan, which has had de facto autonomy since a Kurdish uprising against the Baghdad regime following the January-February 1991 Gulf war. She worked for AFP and the German media, notably the Frankfurter Rundschau and Tagesspiegel newspapers.
